and David Brooks
take on this week in politics,
as we also

27:41.560 --> 27:42.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
examine a Hillary Clinton
presidency in the
second part of our series on how
the candidates

27:42.127 --> 27:43.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
would actually govern.

27:43.862 --> 27:45.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: Two years after the death
of Michael
Brown at the hands of police in
Ferguson,

27:45.597 --> 27:45.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Missouri, the community turns to
a classic
Greek tragedy for a way to
address ongoing

27:45.898 --> 27:47.799 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
issues.

27:47.833 --> 27:49.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRYAN DOERRIES, Co-Founder,
Outside the Wire:
The central question of this
play, "Antigone,"

27:49.434 --> 27:50.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is, what happens when everyone's
right or
feels justified in what they're
doing?

27:50.702 --> 27:50.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
